ntained by a low-frequency\n\n  Line 670: janitor; use it in `ORDER BY`. Trade write amplification for read latency.\n\n  Line 724: **Direction.** Add a config flag (`evaluate.auto_promote`); default to \"propose,\n\n  Line 758:     Janitor[Janitor: decay materialiser, conflict detector, summariser]\n\n  Line 823: provider triggers a one-time re-embed pass via the janitor.\n\n  Line 857: `pending`, surfaced at next SessionStart, accepted/rejected one by one.\n\n  Line 865: existing memories. If `(similarity > 0.85) AND (polarity_opposite OR same_dedup_topic)`,\n\n  Line 866: the new memory is staged `pending` with a link to the conflicting memory. The user\n\n  Line 880:   M -- provenance --> P4[source: user-promotion, importance bumped 3 to 5]\n\n  Line 887: When memory count for a project exceeds a threshold (config), the janitor clusters\n\n  Line 935:     Container(janitor, \"Janitor\", \"Bun scheduler\", \"Decay materialise, conflict detect, rollup propose, sync push/pull\")\n\n  Line 948:   Rel(janitor, dao, \"All access\")\n\n  Line 1002: - Materialise `decay_score` on `memories` (W4); janitor refreshes on a schedule.\n\n  Line 1004:   `pending`.\n\n  Line 1034: | 4 | Adds column (decay_score) | No | New banners only |\n\n  Line 1067:   interface (Phase 3), janitor (Phase 4). Uses §3 (components) and ADRs as\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/UX-SPEC.md:\n  Line 213: | Identical content already stored            | dedup silently | `Reinforced [m_142] (now ✓5).` |\n\n  Line 344: ✓ 003_add_decay_fields     (applied 2026-02-22)\n\n  Line 345: ○ 004_add_provenance       (pending — run /openltm:admin migrate up)\n\n  Line 383: Replaces the deprecated `/openltm:doctor` and `/openltm:decay-report`.\n\n  Line 395: Active: 318  |  Deprecated: 12  |  Last decay run: 2026-04-21\n\n  Line 482: | **User sees** | Nothing currently. (Per PRD §4.3, \"promotes candidate insights for learning\" — happens silently.) |\n\n  Line 512: The proposals would be queued in a `pending_learnings` table; the next\n\n  Line 544:   OR                  + scoped (top      it (implicit          decay\n\n  Line 557:   decay cron          /openltm:admin scan    user runs /memory forget\n\n  Line 583: - **Confirmation:** thumbs-up/down on recall results feeds decay scorer (G-K).\n\n  Line 642: | `/openltm:health`        | Mentioned but not promoted             | 🟡 |\n\n  Line 726: `/openltm:analyze-context` · `/openltm:learn` · `/openltm:decay-report` · `/openltm:capture` ·\n\n  Line 778: | `/openltm:decay-report`    | `/openltm:health`          | output format slightly different — note in warn | v1.6.0 |\n\n  Line 955:        I noticed these patterns across your projects — promote any?\n\n  Line 1031: 2. Same gotcha hit twice → auto-promote to importance 5.\n\n  Line 1081: /ltm forget <id>               ← promote from sub-command\n\n  Line 1082: /ltm init                      ← promote from /openltm:project init\n\n  Line 1103: decay scoring      ← cron in /openltm:health\n\n  Line 1163: - Backing schema for \"pending learnings\" tray (§3.3 EvaluateSession).\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/ROADMAP.md:\n  Line 9: > - `docs/internal/DB-SPEC.md` — schema (pending; section 6 + per-phase DB rows updated when ready)\n\n  Line 30: | Recall scoring at scale | — | W4 | C8 explainer | §8.3 S2 | TBD §4 (decay_score) |\n\n  Line 106: | DB | `memory_audit` schema (pending DB-SPEC §7) |\n\n  Line 123: | DB | `memory_embeddings` table split (pending DB-SPEC §7) |\n\n  Line 135: | Arch | W4 Materialise `decay_score` on memories; janitor refreshes nightly |\n\n  Line 136: | Arch | C6 Memory compression / rollups (low-importance + low-recall → archive table) |\n\n  Line 138: | UX | §8.8 magnificent d