{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780925413113,"sessionID":"ses_158954ac9ffePahLx5YfsvlJLH","part":{"id":"prt_ea76d36f8001DCAAveVq0gHAON","messageID":"msg_ea76d2f75001X6VIsZl4m8cbux","sessionID":"ses_158954ac9ffePahLx5YfsvlJLH","snapshot":"41245d8420945fb7d53012d1b826dfe9cc540151","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1780925418203,"sessionID":"ses_158954ac9ffePahLx5YfsvlJLH","part":{"id":"prt_ea76d4a78001L5y6TqJ9sBxqC4","messageID":"msg_ea76d2f75001X6VIsZl4m8cbux","sessionID":"ses_158954ac9ffePahLx5YfsvlJLH","type":"text","text":"I found the current recall path does consume `decay_score` for default ordering, so this is not just an aspirational doc item.","time":{"start":1780925418104,"end":1780925418202},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_033737ff0b8c6aa5016a26c3ea113481919c31ebdc7cfca70f","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780925418890,"sessionID":"ses_158954ac9ffePahLx5YfsvlJLH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_8qkOryUfCLOYsqPn708vQuzQ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/05-commands.md","offset":86,"limit":40},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/05-commands.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n86: ## `/openltm:admin` — maintenance\n87: \n88: | Subcommand | What it does |\n89: |------------|-------------|\n90: | `migrate [status\\|up\\|down\\|reset\\|--legacy]` | Schema migration control + legacy DB detection. `reset` requires confirmation. |\n91: | `scan [--project X] [--dry-run]` | Scan memories for leaked secrets, redact in-place. `--dry-run` is safe. |\n92: | `server [start\\|stop\\|status]` | Start/stop the graph visualization server (port 7332). |\n93: | `audit [--memory-id N] [--op <op>] [--session <id>] [--since <iso>] [--limit N]` | Query the memory write audit log. |\n94: \n95: ### Examples\n96: \n97: ```\n98: /openltm:admin migrate status\n99: /openltm:admin scan --dry-run\n100: /openltm:admin server start\n101: /openltm:admin audit --since 2026-06-01T00:00:00Z\n102: ```\n103: \n104: `scan` redacts API keys, tokens, and passwords. Always run `--dry-run` first to preview. `migrate reset` drops and recreates the schema — destructive, requires explicit confirmation.\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ## See also\n109: \n110: - [README](../README.md) — back to the top\n111: - [Hooks](06-hooks.md) — the events that fire when commands are used\n112: - [MCP Tools](08-mcp-tools.md) — the underlying tool surface that the commands wrap\n113: - [Configuration](04-configuration.md) — `injectTopN`, `semanticFallback`, `autoRelate`\n\n(End of file - total 113 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"## `/openltm:admin` — maintenance\n\n| Subcommand | What it does |\n|------------|-------------|\n| `migrate [status\\|up\\|down\\|reset\\|--legacy]` | Schema migration control + legacy DB detection. `reset` requires confirmation. |\n| `scan [--project X] [--dry-run]` | Scan memories for leaked secrets, redact in-place. `--dry-run` is safe. |\n| `server [start\\|stop\\|status]` | Start/stop the graph visualization server (port 7332). |\n| `audit [--memory-id N] [--op <op>] [--session <id>] [--since <iso>] [--limit N]` | Query the memory write audit log. |\n\n### Examples\n\n```\n/openltm:admin migrate status\n/openltm:admin scan --dry-run\n/openltm:admin server start\n/openltm:admin audit --since 2026-06-01T00:00:00Z\n```\n\n`scan` redacts API keys, tokens, and passwords. Always run `--dry-run` first to preview. `migrate reset` drops and recreates the schema — destructive, requires explicit confirmation.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/05-commands.md","text":"## `/openltm:admin` — maintenance\n\n| Subcommand | What it does |\n|------------|-------------|\n| `migrate [status\\|up\\|down\\|reset\\|--legacy]` | Schema migration control + legacy DB detection. `reset` requires confirmation. |\n| `scan [--project X] [--dry-run]` | Scan memories for leaked secrets, redact in-place. `--dry-run` is safe. |\n| `server [start\\|stop\\|status]` | Start/stop the graph visualization server (port 7332). |\n| `audit [--memory-id N] [--op <op>] [--session <id>] [--since <iso>] [--limit N]` | Query the memory write audit log. |\n\n### Examples\n\n```\n/openltm:admin migrate status\n/openltm:admin scan --dry-run\n/openltm:admin server start\n/openltm:admin audit --since 2026-06-01T00:00:00Z\n```\n\n`scan` redacts API keys, tokens, and passwords. Always run `--dry-run` first to preview. `migrate reset` drops and recreates the schema — destructive, requires explicit confirmation.\n\n---\n\n## See also\n\n- [README](../README.md) — back to the top\n- [Hooks](06-hooks.md) — the events that fire when commands are used\n- [MCP Tools](08-mcp-tools.md) — the underlying tool surface that the commands wrap\n- [Configuration](04-configuration.md) — `injectTopN`, `semanticFallback`, `autoRelate`","lineStart":86,"lineEnd":113,"totalLines":113,"truncated":false}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/05-commands.md","time":{"start":1780925418879,"end":1780925418889}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_033737ff0b8c6aa5016a26c3ea2c4c8191858c43f367f47d29"}},"id":"prt_ea76d4add001T6Sj7wqkdW36MI","sessionID":"ses_158954ac9ffePahLx5YfsvlJLH","messageID":"msg_ea76d2f75001X6VIsZl4m8cbux"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1780925419263,"sessionID":"ses_158954ac9ffePahLx5YfsvlJLH","part":{"id":"prt_ea76d4efc001u3KpZSfg8OAzhg","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"849456f4e81ed27bbb4e4c5c32338df41befe773","messageID":"msg_ea76d2f75001X6VIsZl4m8cbux","sessionID":"ses_158954ac9ffePahLx5YfsvlJLH","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":94702,"input":2863,"output":105,"reasoning":86,"cache":{"write":0,"read":91648}},"cost":0}}
